inn1.comm: full and off the pads to square leg
terrible delivery, wide full toss and hammered through point for four
much better, on a length just outside off and left alone
back of a length on a similar line and blocked back up the wicket
tucked to point from a similar delivery
ends with a good one, shaping away from Warner and beating his defensive push from the crease
full and the ball shaping away, Watson forward to angle down to third man
full and wide, Warner chased it, swung and missed
tighter line and blocked into the covers
length outside off and left alone
wide and perhaps not short enough to cut and Warner just slaps it into the ground
length and this comes back to strike the pad, a brief cry for lbw but too high, good delivery that
full and clipped powerfully not wide enough of mid on who slides and saves well to his right
a cracker, squaring Warner up and beating him outside the off stump, great length and left him
full and striking the pad, the umpire doesn't signal anything so reckons Warner hit this, was close otherwise, might have missed off stump anyway but he did hit it, another excellent delivery
another good length, Watson forward to drive gets an inside edge past the stumps to square leg
back of a length, Warner stays back and blocks
too straight now and off the pad wide of Kieswetter for a single
full again causes problems for Warner, he swings across a full straight ball that just misses the inside edge and the off stump
length and pushed to point
short and pulled to mid on, wasn't timed
pulled again towards mid on but this goes under Cook and away for four, probably wasn't a chance but it was an awkward one that he couldn't get behind
full outside off played forward off the outer half of the bat to third man, Finn scrambles well to save two
off stump and blocked

and there is the wicket! Pulled straight up and into the hands of square leg. It was short and slightly wide, Warner tried to fetch it to leg and was late on the stroke, getting a top edge that looped up to square leg. Big wicket for England and the extra pace of Finn tells again
forward to drive powerfully to mid off
back of a length and guided down nicely to third man
angled in, off the pad down the leg side but no shot offered so dead ball
half-forward to block into the covers just outside off stump
striking the pad again as Forrest looked to turn a length ball to leg
full and leg side and whipped past midwicket, poor ball nicely put away

full and driven at, edged and dropped in the gully and it's Trott to put the catch down. It was angled in and the drive produced a very thick edge but a diving Trott couldn't hold it going to his right, it was a good height and a bad miss
forward to block on off stump
oh lovely, just guided away from a length outside off past point, super timing
and now cut for four more, that was short and wide and hammered away
length and blocked around off stump
off stump and blocked coming forward
forward and blocked to point, better footwork
back of a length now and blocked
blocked in a similar region
little straight and whipped out to long leg
short and drifts down leg side for a wide, was that actually out of the batsman's reach? Seemed to be very close to leg stump but rules are rules
forward blocking on a length on off stump
bumper and swayed outside the line
wide of off stump and Forrest goes a long way out to follow it as it just shaped away, a goodun
length around off stump, blocked to midwicket
fuller and blocked to mid off
full and driven again to mid off
blocked with soft hands around off stump
back of a length, tried to be guided to third man again, comes off high on the pad and towards slip who parries on the bounce
turned off a length to long leg
forward and blocked around off stump
guided to third man from quite a tight line, stayed leg side of the ball and chopped it down
leg side wide
blocked around off stump
left this time outside off
starts with a wide loosener and gets slapped through extra cover
full and driven again, the stumps do the fielding at the non-striker's end
played forward towards mid on and they scamper through for a sharp single
this is better for Forrest, flicked wide of mid on for three on the front foot
leg side and tickled for four
forward and blocked around off stump
full on middle and leg and flicked behind square on the leg side
forward and blocked to mid off
leg stump and worked to deep square leg
nice-looking drive and blocked by Broad getting down low well
back of a length, tried to be pulled but he played over the top of it, wasn't quite short enough
length and pushed to point from outside off
length outside off and pushed to point
length and worked down to long leg, Finn comes across quickly to field
length outside off and pushed to point
worked from middle and leg down to long leg
length on middle and off, coming forward to block
little bit of width and a back of a length ball chopped to third man
off stump line, tucked to midwicket with a typically-Watson big stride forward
played back up the wicket to a length ball
length and dropped through midwicket, they scramble well for two
driven off an inside edge past the stumps to long leg, Bresnan slides and saves the boundary
leg side, off the pad and they take two more, excellent running again
width outside off on a length and a lovely stroke through extra cover for four
tucked to midwicket from a full length
wide of off stump and guided to third man
played forward and blocked to cover
dropped in front of mid off and they take a quick single
bumper and ducked
played forward towards mid off for no run
length turned down to long leg

great catch! And Broad strikes, it was dug in and Forrest looked to pull, it came off the face of the bat and a diving Kieswetter snaffled it with one hand, superb take. Seemed to be beaten for pace there Forrest, he looked to help it on its way but ended up brushing it behind where he was very well taken
bumper and ducked
length and pushed into the covers
down the leg side, brushes the body and falls short of the keeper
no-ball and pulled out to deep square leg
and now it's a leg side wide
full and straight slapped between cow corner and long on, they take two
cut a touch loosely in the air down to third man, they charge back for two, good running, big boundaries to work with at The Oval
leg side off the pad to fine leg for four
much better line, fourth stump, and driven to point
better again, enticing a push outside off stump and a play and miss to a length ball
blocked solidly on off stump now
forward to block off inside edge and pad now around off stump
short and wide, cut and missed
leg side wide

forward, struck on the pad and given out! It looked good, did he get outside the line, it's referred, it was hit on the knee roll, going over? Yep it is, a good referral by Watson, the ball going over leg stump according to Hawk Eye, only just though, a millimetre from the bail
forward to solidly block now to a similar line
another leg side wide
full and wide of off stump, driven off an inside edge behind square on the leg side for a single to long leg
back of a length and blocked down the wicket
stayed back to cut into the off side but can only find cover
cut hard down to third man
full and wide, swung at and missed
another leg side wide, there have been quite a few by England so far, hasn't been the most disciplined bowling display
full and tucked to midwicket where they run on a misfield
forward on off stump and pushed up to mid off
guided down behind square on the off side for a single
short and cut for four
full and played into midwicket

forward, another large lbw shout was it pad first? It was given not out but England refer this, outside the line for me. It's definitely pad first but he was outside off stump, not the best referral from England
too straight and with long leg up in the circle that is a very poor line, flicked for four
full and pushed into the off side
they take a very very sharp single to midwicket and a direct hit gets him but the back-hand throw from Bell misses coming in from mid on, a poor run
length outside off and left
full and swung just past midwicket for four, a diving Bell couldn't get there
blocked into the off side
slower ball, waited for and cut down to third man
length and blocked around off stump
length and driven to mid off, that was timed quite well
slower ball, Clarke defends and gets an outside edge that runs fine to third man
chopped to third man for a single
angled in, Clarke blocks forward off inside edge and pad to midwicket

but this is edged behind! Goodness me I did not expect that, a little cutter outside off and Clarke feathers it low to Kieswetter. It was a good length and Clarke pushed at it and got a thing edge through to the keeper, good area from Bopara and a mistake from Clarke
back-cut to third man, told you it was easy runs
length and pushed to point
played to the square fielder again
length, back foot punch to the right of Swann
outside off, cut in front of the the cover sweeper
tucked to midwicket
length and worked into the leg side
a skip down and clipped back to the bowler
forward outside off and blocked
full and driven down off an edge to third man
third man fielding again
pushed through the covers to the man in the deep
played forward outside off into the off side
forward and blocked just outside off stump
full and played back up the wicket, saved by a diving Bopara to his right-hand side
forward to a length ball and blocked back to the bowler
outside off, turned to midwicket
the slider and it beats the late cut outside off
outside off again and Bell dives and saves at midwicket, a fine save
thick outside edge as Forrest looked to flick away down the ground I think, through cover for one
firmly played to midwicket
length around off stump and blocked
blocked in a similar area
back of a length, a little straight and worked down to long leg
full and blocked back up the wicket
guided past gully to third man
goes for the pull and gets it square on the leg side
flighted, on the stumps and stays a bit low, Bailey chips the ball back and it doesn't fall far short of Swann
on the stumps, worked into the leg side
tossed up and punched down to long-on
flighted, on the stumps, played down the wicket
bit of air outside off, can't work it past Swann on the drive
full and straight, not much turn but again Watson can't get him away again
good length ball outside off stump, no stroke
short of a length, swings this round the corner for one to deep backward square leg
pitched up and wide of the timbers, Watson leans out and drives through cover to the sweeper
tight line on off, good length, jabbed towards cover
touch short, angling back in from outside off, tries to cut but bottom-edges short on the off side
back of a length, pushed in front of point, Bailey goes charging out of his crease but is sent back before anything untoward can occur
tossed up and turned through midwicket
defended on the front foot in front of off
full and the batsman comes out, drives to long-on on the walk
flighted on the stumps, clips wide of mid-on, good work in the deep stops them coming back for two
tossed up on middle, tickled back past the bowler
flatter, on off and spinning across, worked with the turn through midwicket
length ball on the stumps, whipped through the leg side
defended outside off on a good length
length, coming back in at the stumps, Bailey tries to heave him back down the ground but plays a massive air shot instead
pushed into the off side off a good length
length delivery, punched to extra-cover, again Bailey can't pierce the infield
on the stumps, wicket-to-wicket stuff, knocked to long-on
full and on the stump, turned to short midwicket
tossed up on middle and Bailey misses with a sweep, hit on the pad but the ball was sliding down leg
on off stump, can't beat the close fielder with a nudge to leg
flighted, driven down the ground to long-on
flatter, pushed through on off, stays back a shovels to midwicket
tossed up around off, clipped through midwicket for a single
good length ball, decent pace and beats the outside edge, genuine teaser from Bopara
slightly fuller, on the stumps, pushed back down the ground
length and darting back, cuts Bailey in half and thumps into the knee roll - looked a decent appeal but may have been just missing leg
steered down to third man from outside off
on the stumps, turned to midwicket
full toss, actually more like a beamer - called on height
length ball outside off, pushed to cover

lofted, high towards deep midwicket and Finn takes the catch low the ground ... Watson goes! Swann tempted Watson out of his crease, maybe dragged the length down a smidge, the batsman heaved high but it's a long boundary and Finn plunged forward to claim it
tossed up, can't beat midwikcet with a nudge
full and on off, played back to the bowler, hint of a leading edge
down the leg side, goes back, gets a tickle the ball and it runs away to the fine boundary
tossed up, defended into the off side
flighted, on the stumps, can't beat the infield with a glance to leg
good length outside off, left alone
pitched up, driven square and fielded by point, whose throw to the non-striker's end is a direct hit, the deflection also successfully fielded
defended in front of the stumps
fuller length, gets forward and drops one short on the off side
full and straight, driven to mid-on - Bailey's going to explode any minute now, I can feel it
on the stumps, played back past the bowler for one to long-on - see, I told you. Bailey loves the single to long-on
tossed up on off, dabbed to midwicket
uses the feet this time, working a flatter ball behind square leg to rotate the strike
tossed up, played back to the bowler
flighted outside off, pushed short of point, who comes in
tossed up outside the line of off, driven through cover this time
length ball, spinning towards leg, clipped straight to midwicket
pitched up outside off, Hussey is busy in the crease and gets forward to punch through the covers for a couple
short ball, targeting the batsman, who ducks out of the way
full and straight, can't get this past extra-cover
touch full, played on the front foot to point
length delivery, off-stump line and Hussey opens the face to glide one to third man
full and straight, Bailey misdirects his drive, the bat turning in his hands as the ball skews through square leg
length ball on the stumps, played back to the bowler
slides down the leg side - that's a wide
full and straight, searching for the yorker, Bailey squeezes it to midwicket as the tails in at his toes
pitched up on off, basically a half volley and Bailey dispatches his second four of the innings back down the ground
length ball, defended in front of the stumps
slower ball, out the back of the hand, Bailey waits on it and finds a gap at midwicket
length ball, coming back in towards the top of off, dabbed short of the leg side but the field close in
length ball, chopped to the man at point
shorter, following the batsman, deflects off the gloves on to the wicket and they take one as Broad follows through to field
sliding down the leg side, rolls away off the pads short on the leg side
full and straight - hint of reverse swing? - defended back to the bowler
slides too far down leg and Hussey misses with a flick
length ball in the corridor, steered down to third man
pitched up, on middle and leg, Hussey misses with a glance and the ball deflects into the off side off the pad
touch shorter, chopped short on the leg side
length ball, on off, dribbled short of mid-on and they scamper one
defended into the off side on the back foot
length ball outside off, tailing in towards the stumps, chopped to point
good slower ball from Dernbach, hits Hussey on the pads as he tried to work through midwicket, would have missed leg but chalk that up as a victory to the bowler
length ball outside off, pushed towards point
Bailey gets turned around trying to play through leg from well outside off, thick edge flies over point for a couple
pitched up and shovelled back down the ground in the air, past Finn's dive and beating mid-on ... an ugly but effective shot, just what Bailey needed
on the pads this time and neatly deflected down to fine leg - that'll get the worm twitching
back of a length, pushed short of cover on the back foot for a single
pitched up outside off and pushed to cover on the front foot
full and straight, chipped in the over over midwicket, falls short of the man in the deep - more signs of Bailey attempting to get a wriggle on
pitched up and worked through midwicket
slightly overpitched, on the stumps and picked up quickly, clean strike of the ball back down the ground, no man out and the ball bounces once for four to long-on
slower ball, nudged into the leg side
pitched up outside off, hint of reverse, miscued to midwicket
slow full toss outside off stump and Bailey doesn't mess about, carting a cross-batted shot over mid-on for the third boundary of the over
full and straight, turned short on the leg side
short and wide and slapped hard through point ... well, would have been if Morgan hadn't cut it off superbly
banged in short and pulled agriculturally through midwicket
another back-of-a-length delivery, scooped over the infield, Finn gets round at deep midwicket but had collided with the boundary rope by the time he got to the ball
clipped through square leg, a lot of bottom hand, worth another couple
full and outside off, slides this down to third man with an open face
tossed up on off, spinning in, goes back and drives through cover - there's Bailey's half-century, valuable, no matter how long it's taken
tossed up, worked off the pads through the midwicket region
flighted, clipped through midwicket, good running puts pressure on the fielder
steered through the off side this time and another couple to deep backward point
flighted on off, driven down the ground to long-on

full and juicy, Bailey goes big ... it's not got the legs to clear the rope but returns to earth between Bresnan at deep midwicket and Morgan at long-on. Bresnan perhaps hesitated and couldn't quite get his hands to the catch, despite throwing himself full length
full and squeezed out through point
on the stumps, shovelled over the infield to deep cover
blocked in front of the stumps, Bailey wanted a run, had to turn back as Bopara fielded, missed with a throw at the non-striker's end and they get one anyway
length ball outside off, Bailey fails to connect with a big old heave
slow bouncer, waits on it and pulls to deep midwicket
low full toss, shovelled to mid-on, they want two but won't get them this time
driven back, Broad fields but only deflects the ball on to Bailey, the ball scooting away behind the stumps and they take one
full and straight, the ball bobbles away off the pad
pitched up and punched to long-off
short ball, pulled through midwicket
pitched up outside off, driven hard to the cover sweeper, who misfields slightly, the batsmen get two
Hussey backs away, Broad drags the ball short and takes the pace off, clubbed for one to long-on

full and wide, hoicked back at the bowler, who half stops the ball, turns, scrambles, throws at one stump ... and gone! Brilliant work from Finn, leaving Hussey yards short and squeezing the boot back on Australia's collective throat
full and straight, nudged short of cover
and it's the fastest one of the match so far, pitching on a length, rising and leaving Wade, who gets nowhere near it
down the leg side, clips the pad and rolls behind square
on the stumps, maybe trying for the slower ball, Bailey times this delightfully off his pads through deep backward square for the first boundary in four overs
on the stumps, pushed back down the ground for one
full and straight, lofted over the infield for one to long-off
length ball, angled across the lefty, tries to dab into the off side and it ends up at short leg, they take one anyway
low full toss, Bailey had shuffled across and clips the ball straight to short fine leg - if he'd missed that would have been curtains
on the stumps, worked through the leg side
touch short and room for Wade to swing those lumberjack forearms, slicing a cut shot thorugh point and away to the rope
full length, on leg stump, hits the pad and rolls square - Broad appeals but it probably was just outside the line
full and straight, punched down the ground to long-off

another full bunger and bowled 'im! Excellent death delivery from Bresnan, pitched up and asking the batsman to take a chance - Bailey did but his heave-ho was unsuccessful, the timbers sounding a death rattle
short ball to Lee first up, dabbed to third man
full and wide, Wade has to reach to jam his bat down on it and Bresnan tidies up in his follow-through

another one down, caught a short fine leg trying to ramp the ball over the infield! Bresnan's length has been hard to hit, Wade tried to improvise but couldn't clear the man. Bresnan looks like a man who's found a twinkie down the back of the sofa
length ball, sliced through the covers
full and quick to start with, dug out for one back past the bowler
full toss, wide of the stumps and Dernbach gets away with it as Johnson swings and misses
another low full toss, this time carved through cover-point
slower ball, slogged down the ground and Morgan drops it at long-on - perhaps had half an eye on the rope, he was that close, but should've been taken
full toss, clubbed through the off side as Lee steps away
pitched up and chopped back down the ground, the ball clipping Lee at the non-striker's end on its way
full and again swiped down the ground - Lee has to jump out of the way again
low full toss and this time Lee middles it, fetching the ball a long way over the rope at long-on. BOOM!
pitched up on off, driven to mid-off
full and wide of the stumps, dug out towards long-off, they think about two but think again
more yorker-length stuff, drilled to long-on but can't get under it
full and straight again and chopped back past the bowler for one
pitched up and shovelled back down the ground
slower ball, on the stumps, Lee swings hard, comes off the toe of the bat and loops short of Morgan this time, coming in from long-off, the ball skips past him and they come back for two
length ball on off, frees the arms again but gets an inside edge to backward square leg
another slow delivery from Dernbach, worked into a gap in front of midwicket
length delivery, Johnson has a golf swing at it, hit on the pad and it slides away towards the slip - Dernbach appeals but it probably pitched outside the line

slower ball, out of the back of the hand, Lee shovels the ball skyward again, it's coming down between long-on and long-off ... Morgan gets there but can't cling on as his body hits the turf, the ball popping free and allowing Lee to pick up three

inn2.comm: full and wide, left alone
full and squirted down to third man to get England away
tight line on off stump, blocked back to the bowler
leg side short ball, a brief cry for caught behind as Bell hooked a little late and missed, a wide perhaps? Not given
back of a length and chopped in front of point, they take three out to the cover rope
back of a length and blocked back up the wicket
starts on middle and leg and Bell clips him to square leg
dropped into the leg side and they scramble a run but Cook was struggling had Johnson thrown down the stumps at the striker's end, that would have been gone
full and left outside off, it's a no-ball so a cheer goes up and a free hit will follow
goes full and Cook whips it away through extra cover, well placed
good length just outside off, left alone
width offered and it's cut down to third man
length, dropped into the leg side for no run
just outside off, pushed at and missed
wide down leg side, fumbled by Wade who parries it away but it runs past short long leg for four
angled down to third man
off stump and blocked to cover
full and pushed to point from just outside off
back of a length and played to point again
length and dropped wide of mid off for a single
length and strikes the pad, another no ball!
step to leg and slapped over mid off for four, that was a good strike, gave himself room and swung through the line
responds with a goodun, shaping away and beating the outside edge
short and tucked wide of square leg on the pull, it wasn't timed, but in the gap and they get three
left outside off
cut hard, into the ground, to point
another no-ball! Oh deary me. And this is wide and slapped through cover for four, nicely put away by Cook
but this time only an edge into the boot and no run back to the bowler
middle stump line and tucked in front of mid on coming forward
just outside off and dropped into the leg side
forward just outside off, played to point
Bell shuffles down but blocks around off stump
outside off this time but Bell's cut misses
large cry for leg before, probably going down, not out and they don't review
shot! Wide half-volley and timed away past the infield and it will run away for four, lovely stroke
now shorter on off stump, pushed nearly wide enough of mid on but it was just about saved with a slide
full and played back to the bowler
same again
touch wider this time so Bell can open the face and guide to the cover sweeper
played into the leg side from a length on middle stump

and there is a wicket with Cook caught on the crease and plumb lbw. Boy did Australia need that. Excellent delivery, good length around off stump, it shaped back to beat the forward push of Cook and caught him around the knee roll bang in front of middle
length outside off and left alone
full and pushing at it was Trott, played and missed
just outside off again, angled into the gully, played quite late
good line again just outside off, left alone
cut on the bounce to point
full and dropped in front of point, Bell sends Trott back
forward to block around off stump
this time they do take the single in front of point
front foot driven attractively past extra cover into the deep for a single
forward and blocked again
driven down to long off
driving forward and edged but short and wide enough of slip, it runs away for four, another good un on a great length and just nibbled away from Bell
length and pushed at and missed outside off, felt for
a step down but just forward and blocked back to the bowler
step down again and blocked down to mid on
full driven off an inside edge back to the bowler
blocked again into the off side
full on middle and leg, pushed out through square on the leg side for a couple
forward to block up on the off side
just outside off and Trott gets down with a reverse paddle fine for four, hell of a shot
forward and blocked again
middle and leg but this flick finds midwicket
toss up outside off and ran to extra cover
length just outside off, dropped to point
Bell stepped down again and blocked a length ball back to the bowler
pushed square on the off side from a length
outside off, guided to third man
too full and wide enough for Trott to get out to it and drive past extra cover for four, well timed
chopped into the ground and it balloons over gully to third man
played forward on middle and off back to the bowler
played to point from a length around off stump
a step to leg and a tuck past midwicket, very Trott, doesn't go for four but more runs to tick the score along
short and leg side, comes off the thigh pad I think and runs very fine past the wicketkeeper for four, caught Bell on the hip in fact
forward and blocked to point
middle stump line, Bell comes forward and plays into midwicket for a single
length ball, sliding towards leg stump, closes the face for one through square leg
line and length outside off stump, pushed towards cover coming forward
drifts too far down leg - that's a wide
pitched up outside the line of off, driven in front of square
defended into the off side from a good length ball

edged and taken ... but it didn't quite carry to Wade! Bell opened the face, trying to guide the ball to third man, got a thick edge but if bounced just short of the wicketkeeper's outstretched right hand
straighter line, turned through midwicket
full and straight, blocked into the on side
length ball, angled across the right-hander, pushed towards cover
back of a length, deflected down on to the wicket, via bat and pad, playing back
fuller length, nudged into a gap between point and cover
bouncer, wide of off, stays back and dabs the ball to third man for a single
pitched short, sliding across and inside-edged behind square on the leg side
skips out and bangs a Dorothy straight back down the ground! Length ball, nothing wrong with it, but Bell left his crease and boffed it over long-off with the bat held high
length ball on the stumps, turned to the fielder at square leg
wide of the stumps, hangs back and steers behind point for one
length ball on off, gets forward and punches back to the bowler

Trott advances on Watson, gets a faint inside edge, and the ball rattles the stumps! The ball was pretty similar to the one Bell hit out of the park but Trott played with an angled bat - where Bell's was straight - and Watson skidded it through the gap to disturb wicket. Trott's off and Aussies/aesthetes everywhere rejoice
length ball, opens the face and edges low to slip on the bounce, managed to keep it down
beats of a ball from Johnson, rearing off a length and spearing past Bell as he plays back - but Johnson, to jeers from the crowd, had overstepped again
fired across, slightly full and Bell clubs to mid-on, trying to get under it and clear the infield
length ball outside off, pushed through the covers for an easy single
angled across the right-hander, who dabs it to third man
full and a touch of inswing for Johnson, rapping Bopara on the front pad as he stepped outside the line of off
short and defended into the off side
length ball, sliding across, walks across and toe-ends a single to third man
length ball outside off, stays back a prods into the covers
straighter line, Bopara takes the ball from around off through midwicket off a good length
length ball, played back to the bowler
touch short of a good length, on the line of off, shows it the maker's name
shortish, slightly wide, tapped through point to the sweeper
defended into the leg side
length ball, pushed through the covers
pitched up around off, blocked into the on side
short delivery, Bopara quickly into position to swivel-pull, finds backward short leg but they run hard for one
another quick single, this time after Bell tickles one into the leg side
fast and straight outside the line of off, steered behind point with soft hands
clipped off the pads towards midwicket, in the air but drops short
length ball, Bopara checks the ball in the air back down the pitch but it's to Watson's right and dies on him anyway
full and on leg stump, hits the pads but would have been missing
length outside off, guides it down to third man
tight line, beats the outside edge and goes in an out of Wade's gloves - Watson thought there might have been an edge but it was almost as close to bowling Bell
touch shorter, worked through the leg side
length ball on off, opens the face and runs to third man
length ball, pushed into the off side
short of a length outside off, tapped behind square on the off side
length delivery on the stumps, blocked into the leg side
line drifts across, Bell clips a half-volley through square leg
short of a length, Bopara angles his bat and guides a pull through deep backward square for his first boundary - that's the hundred up too
another bumper, gets big on him and this pull shot is less controlled, flying to long leg on the bounce
pitched up on middle and whipped wristily through square leg, good placement and they run three
length ball outside off, defended back on to the wicket
bit of width and Bell rocks back to thrash a cut shot through square, the ball rasping past the despairing dive of the man at point
touch short, on the stumps, turned through midwicket
